        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 7:37PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 736 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lela, or 8 miles west of Shamrock, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wheeler, Kellerville, and Lela.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
